<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,462,667]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,462,487]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In addition to the characters given in the first couplet of the key, the foreleg tibia has soft, helmet-like setae (at least in males) and a long tibial epiphysis, and the 
<number box="[825,837,498,523]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="8.0">8</number>
th abdominal sternite in the males is densely covered with sharp setae. Larvae feed mainly on 
<taxonomicName box="[605,719,535,558]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Moraceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,462,667]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,570,595]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Distribution.</emphasis>
Widely distributed around the world except the New World and Western Europe. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,606,631]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
Two lineages can be recognized within the subfamily: the 
<taxonomicName box="[999,1089,606,631]" class="Insecta" family="Bombycidae" genus="Bombyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[999,1089,606,631]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Bombyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group and the 
<taxonomicName box="[1342,1435,607,630]" class="Insecta" family="Bombycidae" genus="Ocinara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1342,1435,607,630]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ocinara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1713,1765]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,227,1713,1734]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Map 
<number box="[208,221,1713,1734]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[388,470,1713,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Bombycidae" genus="Bombyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[388,470,1713,1735]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Bombyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. mainly in 
<collectingCountry box="[626,690,1713,1735]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">China</collectingCountry>
. * 
<taxonomicName box="[712,788,1714,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Bombycidae" genus="Bombyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mori">
